
SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE HOUSTON/GALVESTON TX 859 
PM CDT SAT MAY 12 2001

THE NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE HAS ISSUED A

* SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING FOR...   NORTHERN HARRIS COUNTY IN SOUTHEAST 
TEXAS

* UNTIL 945 PM CDT

* AT 857 PM CDT...DOPPLER RADAR INDICATED A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM 5   MILES 
NORTHWEST OF SPRING...MOVING SOUTH AT 15 MPH.

* LOCATIONS IN THE PATH OF THE SEVERE THUNDERSTORM INCLUDE...   HOOKS 
AIRPORT   SPRING   BUSH-INTERCONTINENTAL AIRPORT...HUMBLE   ALDINE

MOVE TO AN INTERIOR ROOM ON THE LOWEST FLOOR OF YOUR HOME OR BUSINESS. STAY 
AWAY FROM WINDOWS!

PLEASE REPORT SEVERE WEATHER TO THE COUNTY SHERIFF...LOCAL POLICE... OR 
DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC SAFETY. THEY WILL RELAY YOUR REPORT TO THE NATIONAL 
WEATHER SERVICE.